oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Copperhill depot
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of the Copperhill depot in Polk County, showing a train coming down the tracks. John Hyatt, a mailman, is standing on the platform along with another man, and a woman is standing in the doorway of the station building.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Railroad stations; Covered wagons
